    <p>
      <i>
        <sup>1</sup>
      </i>
      <i>Reported and adjusted OCI margins are calculated as reported and adjusted OCI, respectively, divided by revenues net of excise taxes.</i>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Shipment Volume</b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Third Quarter</b>
    </p>
    <ul class="bwlistdisc">
      <li>
Smokeable products segment reported domestic cigarette shipment volume decreased 11.6%, primarily driven by the industry’s decline rate (impacted by macroeconomic pressures on ATC disposable income and the growth of illicit e-vapor products), retail share losses, calendar differences and trade inventory movements.

</li>
      <li>
When adjusted for calendar differences and trade inventory movements, smokeable products segment domestic cigarette shipment volume decreased by an estimated 10%.

</li>
      <li>
When adjusted for trade inventory movements, calendar differences and other factors, total estimated domestic cigarette industry volume decreased by an estimated 8%.

</li>
      <li>
Reported cigar shipment volume increased 2.7%.

</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <b>First Nine Months</b>
    </p>
    <ul class="bwlistdisc">
      <li>
Smokeable products segment reported and adjusted domestic cigarette shipment volume decreased 10.5%, primarily driven by the industry’s decline rate (impacted by macroeconomic pressures on ATC disposable income and the growth of illicit e-vapor products) and retail share losses.

</li>
      <li>
When adjusted for trade inventory movements and other factors, total estimated domestic cigarette industry volume decreased by an estimated 8%.

</li>
      <li>
Reported cigar shipment volume increased 4.2%.

</li>
    </ul>
